The paper proposes statistical hypothesis tests for detecting changes in the covariance structure of Gaussian Processes (GPs) and uses them to improve Bayesian Online Change Point Detection (BOCPD). This work involves machine learning and statistical analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with time series data and change point detection, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.ST (Statistics). The use of statistical hypothesis tests and Bayesian methods also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information theory and signal processing, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
